<p>W3C owns and manages the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2</a>.
</p>
<p>WCAG 2.2 was published in October 2023. You’ll need to comply with the new criteria no later than October 2024. See
  more about <a href="https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/helping-people-to-use-your-service/understanding-wcag">Meeting
    government accessibility requirements</a> in the GOV.UK Service Manual.</p>

<h2>Updates to our Design System</h2>
<p>We’ve made changes to comply with WCAG 2.2 level AA. You must check if your service needs amending to align with
  these changes.</p>

